  <title class="- topic/title ">Add a Host to the Host List</title>
  <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">To recognize a host, certain conditions
	 must be met. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Target" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Advanced" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
    <p class="- topic/p ">
      <ul id="ul_35A3B9EB62FD48B1B82DCA88880A7D34" class="- topic/ul ">
        <li id="li_1CD6DED0B6974817B4126BDB1A52632D" class="- topic/li "> The
		  mbox.js for your account must be saved one of your directory 
		</li>
        <li id="li_07EAF519B38643B79D976743B4DAF830" class="- topic/li "> At
		  least one mbox must exist on the host 
		</li>
        <li id="li_50533ACDE72C4F1B8F8A5AE48DD54E34" class="- topic/li "> A page
		  on the host must have 
		  <ul id="ul_6F48AF476C2340D89A7893E020DB8FAB" class="- topic/ul "><li id="li_0A898AD218AD4B16B0EEEB90D25CC389" class="- topic/li "> An
				accurate mbox.js reference 
			 </li><li id="li_65EDE1E683704092AC5AEA4762BC1534" class="- topic/li "> An
				mbox 
			 </li></ul></li>
        <li id="li_25B1CF570C6B43A78A08384DD408AF75" class="- topic/li "> The
		  page with the mbox must be viewed in a browser 
		</li>
      </ul>
    </p>
    <p class="- topic/p ">Once the page is viewed, the host will be listed,
		allowing you to host group as well as preview and launch campaigns and tests. 
	 </p>
    <p class="- topic/p ">
      <note class="- topic/note ">This includes any personal development
		  servers. 
		</note>
    </p>
  </conbody>
